planned c section can someone who has had a planned c section tell me what to expect did you go to the hospital the night before etc thanks no choice in the matter but thanks for the advice like i said someone who has had one need only respond thanks teresa first of all ignore those other idiots telling you to read stuff about c sections you don't need to be listening to flag waving morons i had a planned c section with my nd child here's how it went with me i was scheduled for an am c section i had to be at the hospital by am that gives them time to do the paperwork get you in a room change your clothes etc at am i was taken down to the waiting area on a gurney and sat in the hallway of the or room i think i got an iv and sure enough at am i got rolled into the operating room it was very small and very cold then they ask you to sit up and bend over so they can get a spinal in i had a spinal this time instead of an epidural like with my st as soon as the spinal was in my legs went numb they laid me down but put my legs up and inserted a catheter i was kind of embarrassed but then i realized that it's not any big deal to these doctors and nurses they've been there and done that thousands of times then they put a warm blanket on my chest and arms once i was all ready to go they brought my husband in and they started the c section after the baby is delivered they'll take the baby to the nursery and they'll take you to the recovery room you'll have to stay there until the feeling in your legs comes back i think it took about hours for me to get back to my own room and finally hold my baby in a way it was scary and nervous because i didn't know what to expect but in a way it was kind of nice knowing that i'm having my baby monday morning at am Childbirth Urinary incontinence Shaggy dog story Aerial (dance move) Epidural Effect of Hurricane Katrina on New Orleans Local anesthesia Blood on the Tracks Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Criticism of government res